RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 21000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARTINI MARTIN came away in good order and raced two to three wide into the first turn, remained unhurried off the pace while never too far back, edged a bit closer two wide mid-way around the far turn, shifted to the three path entering upper stretch, responded willingly called upon, seized command near mid-stretch and finished going away. SILENT MODE bobbled outward a step at the start, was forwardly placed two wide heading into the first turn, tracked the pace three deep mid-way up the backstretch, advanced to challenge the leader at the quarter pole, vied with JERSEY PERFECTION to mid-stretch then failed to be a match when the winner swept by. JERSEY PERFECTION rated in early stages then edged up closer racing between foes midway up the backstretch, challenged DANGEROUS MIND for the lead entering the far turn, got by rival then took on SILENT MODE near the quarter pole, vied into upper stretch then gave way. PAPA FUNNY raced up close inside around the first turn, continued forwardly placed up the backstretch, weakened near the inside around the far turn and had no further punch. DANGEROUS MIND led the way around the first turn and set the pace with rivals in close contention up the backstretch, dueled with JERSEY PERFECTION entering the far turn then faded.

ENTRY.NAME: Papa Funny
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close early inside, weakened far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Dangerous Mind
ENTRY.OWNER: Jagger Inc Johnson Troy Lo Charles and Del Toro Eric Nikolaus
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, vied far turn, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Silent Mode
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled outward start, track pace, up 1/4p, vied, no match late

ENTRY.NAME: Jersey Perfection
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated btwn, vied turn-upper, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Martini Martin
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled off pace, bid 3wd 3/16p, pulled away

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 23, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 26, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 26, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REMEMBERING WILBUR sped to the lead at the start and continued to hold a narrow advantage around the turn, came two wide into upper stretch, hustled along two to three wide through the lane, had plenty left in reserve and pulled away. EDWARD MADDEN hustled up out of the gate and raced up close three wide in the early going, edged up closer but could not reach the eventual winner around the turn, continued to chase after rival into the lane and stayed on for second best. HE'S A SHOOTER tracked the top pair in early stages, picked up the tempo three wide nearing the quarter pole, ran on through the lane and secured a share. CREATIVE CLOUD was off a step slow at the start, raced in the back, swung four to five wide into upper stretch and needed more for impact. JIMMY THE KID was not too far back on the inside into the turn, cut the corner entering the lane then gave way. MINISTER QUINN was forwardly placed in early stages, weakened around the turn and had no further response.

ENTRY.NAME: Remembering Wilbur
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, 2wd into stretch, going away

ENTRY.NAME: Creative Cloud
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow start, in back, 4-5wd upper, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: He's a Shooter
ENTRY.COMMENT: in range, move 3pth 1/4p, along for show

ENTRY.NAME: Edward Madden
ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, up close turn, stayed on

SALVO TRIGGER was shuffled back at the start, coaxed along between rivals two deep and lacked a bid.

PESADILLA CHANEL was coaxed along early, raced four wide into the upper stretch and weakened a bit through the drive. DWELLING LEGACY raced two deep around the far turn, continued to race two deep between horses near the three sixteenths pole and had no late rally. IN THE END was quick to begin to sprint clear early and was empty into the upper lane.
